49 Ma Virgilio n’avea lasciati scemi 50 di sé, Virgilio dolcissimo patre, 51 Virgilio a cui per mia salute die’mi;
52 né quantunque perdeo l’antica matre, 53 valse a le guance nette di rugiada, 54 che, lagrimando, non tornasser atre.

query.result:
**English:**
49 But Virgil had left us bereft 50 of himself, Virgil, the sweetest father, 51 Virgil to whom I said for my salvation;
52 nor, however much he lost his ancient mother, 53 did it avail his cheeks, clean of dew, 54 that, weeping, they did not return wet.
**Sanskrit:**
