query.result:
**English:**
127 When from flesh to spirit she had ascended, 128 and beauty and virtue had grown in me, 129 I was less dear and less pleasing to him;
130 and he turned his steps on an untrue path, 131 following false images of good, 132 which fulfill no promise completely.
**Sanskrit:**
127 Yadaḥ śarīrāt prāṇeṣu ārohatī sma, 128 Saundaryam ca guṇaś ca mayi vardhamānaḥ āsīt, 129 Tada aham tasmai alpīyasī priyā alpīyasī ca rocyamānā abhūvam;
130 Sa ca svakān padān mārge mithyānivarttayām āsa, 131 Kalyāṇasya mithyāpratimāḥ anudhavataḥ, 132 Yāḥ śubhāśiṣaḥ samyak na pūrayanti.
